values:
whoop whoop 
 ONLY 2 MORE DAYS TILL MY B-DAY!

HEY HEY GUYS!

SO yep yep life is going good....

I still love my job....although some D-U-M (lol) stuff happened.

school is still ok ...BLAH!

I can't wait for this summer...YEAH!

oh ok so something embarressing...

   On Tuesday I decided to skip out on my math class (lol), and like usual I slept in and  I was running late for english. I was running down the stairs of he parking garage and fell down the stairs. OK so beyond the embarrement factor...I twisted my ankle pretty bad and for some odd reasons I thought that I had developed an acute case of amnesia. So just picture my laying on the ground saying "my name is annie barrett and i live at .....". lol ok yes I agree this is very amusing now but at the time i was so scared I would forget who I am. After I asured myself I knew who I was I then had to devise I plan for getting down 2 more flights of stairs without breaking my neck.... yes yes I know I had to make it look graceful. lol hahahaha well that didn't happen I managed to make it down a few stairs to an elevator where I took that up to my car....
hahahaha yep yep that was my near death experience for the week.
After I had my dad look at it he told to me to go home and put ice on it...but i didn't comply. I went out to lunch with Teresa and Robin from Christian Challenge. 

Right now I'm chillin with Lynsey.
We are talking about old times and I'm trying to help her get ready to move out on her own. All this to say I'm the older one in college helping her get ready for college and she had to teach me how to do laundry....yep yep some how thats ironic ...yes

OK so I should go
talk to ya later gator!
          God Bless!
                Annie

LOVE IS IN THE AIR....
 
ok well not in the air I'm breathing, but for others around me lol.

So Whitney is getting married to Josh!
I'm so happy for them.
I went to her shower on Saturday and I cried....i'm such a girl. 
So the wedding is on May 2nd and I can't wait.
She will make such a beautiful bride!

Michelle and George are getting married!
I don't know when, but yep yep its happening.
I love them both so much and they are good for each other.
I've never seen Chelle like this before, she glows!

Mark and Brielle are such a beautiful couple.
Seeing them together makes me happy!

I also love seeing Anthony and Erin together, cause they are so cute!
I got to get to know Anhtony a little better tonight, and he is coolio in my book. 

Chis and Lynsey are so cute together too!
They are going to be together forver, so I'm sure they are going to hear me say that plenty of times.



AWWWWW YEAH I'M SO HAPPY!


I GOT A JOB!
I work at my church and I love it.

School it going great(amazing i know...)!

GOD IS AMAZING!

Everything is in order and it couldn't be better. 
I know I'm in God's will
   I have a job
   I have a leadership role in the youth group
   I get to be a student leader at camp twice this summer
   School is going well
   God is showing me His plan day by day

I don't mean to brag.....wait yes I do.
 
The bible says to boast in the Lord and let me tell you all these things are only of God.


God is still teaching me things...
   why certain things happen
   why things have to change
   why people turn away
   and not to worry about these things


but i know in the end all the glory goes to God, so its all good yo. lol

Teach me to know that I need you 
Simply because Lord I need you
Not cause I'm tired of what I do
Wow....somethings never change with him, but I wish they would!

Ok so he and I are not great friends anymore!
He is a jerk and is only out for number one.
      So thats fine...I'm done!
He hasn't done anything except change over the past two weeks......OH WELL NOT MY PROBLEM ANYMORE!

   -annie-
P.S. But I'm praying for him...

How odd is it that just when you think you have everything in order things tend to suprise you.
 
So i've noticed that friends from then past are making an appearence in my life lately, and its a good thing.But old friends that you would think you would hold dear and keep forver.....are not friends so much anymore.
Oh well....
what can you do?
 So he and  are good friends and it took a lot out of me to be content with that. 

BLAH!
But guys are jerks!
 
 -annie- 


P.S. I MISS HANNAH!

GOD ROCKS.......and boys stink!

the only two absolute truths in life......BLAH!

So tonight we did the whole true love waits talk at church. 
I love this night more then any other. 
I know I don't need to hear the whole speech each year(I've made the commitment and I'm sticking with it), but I know that there are kids there each year that need that talk like no other.
Pastor Mike does a great job each year with it. 
Its not too serious to where we can laugh and joke around, but at the same time he breaks it down to the truth. 

This week-end was good!

The past 6 months I have been praying about what God wants me to do in the near future. I know that I am supossed to do the whole seminary thing, and I am so excited about that! And I know I'm going to be a counselor at centrifuge next summer and hopefully every summer after that, but my heart was longing for a mission opp. this summer.

So I am praying about taking a year off of school to do some type of mission work. I don't know what, but I totally realized today in church that my life is not my own. And the only way I will be able to let God use me fully is by allowing Him to put me somewhere I have no control over. Where God is in total control of my life and my walk. And the amazing thing is I'm not scared .....I AM SO EXCITED!

So yep yep anyways I'm gonna go, but I'll talk to y'all later gator!

 God Bless!
             -annie-

Find a guy who calls you beautiful instead of hot, who calls you back when you hang up on him, who will stay awake just to watch you sleep. Wait for the boy who kisses your forehead, who wants to show you off to the world when you are in your sweats, who holds your hand in front of his friends, who thinks you're just as pretty without makeup on. Wait for the one who is constantly reminding you of how much he cares about you and how lucky he is to have you. Wait for the one who turns to his friends and says, "...that's her."

I got this from Kellie!
This is so true, so if you care about your heart think about these things. 
Don't just date to date......date to marry!(talk to God about it....DUH! He knows because your future is in His hands)
God Bless!
-annie-

I GOT TO TALK TO HANNAH ON THE PHONE! 

that just made my day!

The past week was fun!

 I still dislike school, but I think by at least my senior year of college I could get use to this...lol.

Friday: we were all supossed to go to the mountains, but the weather was too bad. So Erin, Lance, Kenny, Mark, Seema, Kellie, Brielle, Alex, and I all went to Rock and Java to see Time Spent Burning!  I hadn't heard them in awhile, but THEY WERE STINKIN AWESOME! It is such an encouragment to see amazing men of God up on stage only for God. Yep yep....then we all went to the hang out to play pool. It was ok I guess E.T. showed up lol. I bonded with Brielle, Seema, and Kellie! Good stuff Good stuff! Erin spent the night which rocked and we stayed us forever talking

Saturday: a lot  happened so i'll skip it lol

Sunday: church of course! Riana and I did a skit in church again and it was great. After church Kylee, Kenny, Lance, Jon, Peggy, and I went out to eat. I had girls group at four, and it went really well. Its such a blessing to see girls seious about God and not being fake about it. After youth we all went over to peggy's to watch a movie and then went to the park. Jessi spent the night YEAH!

Monday: Alex woke me up at like 7 am with a text mess.....BLAH! I didn't get any sleep that day...OH WELL! We all went to a funeral for a lady at our church. I didn't really know her that well, but God sure did use her in amazing ways during her life. 
After that we went to Peggy's house to watch a movie:
      Jessi was so sick and I felt so bad for her
      Poor Mark had to work
      Alex elbowed me in the head
      IT RAINED ALL DAY!
Then we were going to go bowling, but ended up at Brielle's house YEAH! It was so much fun! We played pool and watched Cellular. Kellie, Seema, and Brielle crack me up! E.T. showed up again but they took care of it! I spent the night at Peggy's house and we talked forever!

Tuesday: I didn't go to school lol! I went over to Alex's house and hung out with him and Halley. We started to redecorate his room but it didn't work out. Then I picked up Lance from work YEAH i got starbucks lol. Later on Kellie, Brielle, Mark, Lance, Alex, Halley, and I went to sky zone. It was alright....lol. THEN WE DID TACO TUESDAY! We all went back to Brielle's house to play pool and I beat Lance! I had to drag Lance away from the pool table to got o Christian Challenge. Christian Challnge was good....Pastor Mike preached and it was awesome. Then I went home and went to bed!

Wed: I went shopping with grandma! Then at 3 went to alex's house to watch kill bill 2, but I missed the begining....I didn't quite understand why she wanted to kill bill....Then we went to church! Youth group was great last night! I took Erin home and got to see little Elijah! Lance and I went to starbucks, and then I went back over to alex's house to watch the begining of kill bill, so now I kind of understand why she wanted to kill bill. But i didn't like the movie.....the whole plucking out daryl hannah's eye freaked me out. 

So yep yep anyways 
I'm on my way to go shopping with Julia and Alyssa....talk to ya later gator!
          God Bless! 
                    -annie-

Life is great! 

I've realized a lot about my life and my future lately. 

I can't wait for seminary!
I can't wait to be doing what God has planned for me!
I just can't wait, because God has so much in store!

I've also realized many truths in my life...

Truth number one: it is better to have him as an amazing guy friend then anything else!

Truth number two: college really is as important as my parents say.

Truth number three: God gives us experiences(both bad and good) in our lives to learn from, but also      to minister to others that might be going through the same things!

Truth number four: My life isn't about me!

And I've learned to be thankful for blessings I never saw coming...

1.)  SCHOOL!
2.) BROKEN HEARTS!
3.) Learning who my true friends are...
4.) Going through having to learn what a friend is in general...

Well I should go...
I have to go pack for the mountains!

Talk to ya later gator!
  God Bless!
           -annie-

P.S. I was determined to be apethetic about this whole thing, but I do care! And I will continue to care and pray about it...and too bad if you don't like it!

BLAH! 
I dunno.....I just thought I would update. I really don't have anything to say, but I'm sure I'll think of something.

OH YEAH! I got The Notebook yesterday and it is the most amazing movie ever!lol I've watched it like 4 times in the past two days. I CRIED SO MUCH!

We are going to the mountains next week....
I miss how things used to be like 3 years ago....
I miss (the old) Michelle and Christina....
I wish I could go back to highschool sometimes....
I want to go back to Glorietta...


Well on a less depressing note GUYS STILL STINK! lol 

This week-end should be good!
Talk to ya later gator!

God Bless!
 -annie-

ok i know i know....how many times have you heard this from me? 
                             GUYS SUCK!
 
I'm so sick of him!
I'm sick of his lies, his leading me on, and basically just him in general.
I really thought that him and I were getting to be really good friends, but I guess not.......
All i really wanted was for him to be like one of my best guy friends, but he really screwed that up.
But whatever I'm sure I'll be over it by tomorrow lol!
      -annie-

Ok so as of Sunday night I was very upset with all boys in general. I didn't care who you were, but if you were a male I disliked you! Good news God totally brought me out of that! To be honest I don't know why I was so upset but one boy made me so mad that I blammed all the problems of the world on every man. I then talked myself into believeing that I was over a guy that I wasn't really over, which didn't make Sunday night any easier. 

But like I said God brought me out of it. 

Monday was such a bad day to where I found myself wondering why I didn't just stay in bed....
But God gave me the most amazing night that night! I went and spent some time with some of the girls from Christian Challenge and God blessed my heart. Liz Sara, and I had praise band practice and there God mended my broken heart. I then realized that I can't fix everyone or their problems ( no mater how much or often I try). I can't take the trials of other people and put them on my shoulders, but I can encourage them in the Lord to where they let go of their problems and let God take care of the rest. 

Father God, 
     I ask that you use me touch everyone around me. Lord God all I want is for people to see you when they look at me. I no longer long for the earthly desires of my heart but for your will to be done as I make your desires mine. Father God, please reveal yourself to everyone that is on my heart. I want them to come to know you like never before, and for the others to return to you. You know my heart Father and I ask that the only time it will ever break again is for you and your will. 
   I pray all these things in your holy and precious name
                                       amen

HEY HEY Y'ALL!
     This week-end was fun I guess....Friday Lance I hung out at my house until Jessi got home. We went and got Kenny and then went over to Jessi's house. Omg it was so funny! We were driving around and saw this guy and he was so crazy "drinking and driving drinking and driving" lol. Then we cruised the strip which Jessi made it funny. Then we all went home and at about 1:30....I was tired

Saturday: jessie woke me up stinking early because alex and lance had sent me a text mess so my phone kept going off lol. So we got up and went and picked up justin and alex to go do yard work at some ladies house. Thomas and Lance came and helped later on, but we still are not done so we have to go back next week. After that we went to church cause lance and alex had to practice a skit. lol justin, jessi, and I goofed off while they were practicing lol I am so funny! Then we went back to my house to chillax (BRISTI CALLED ME) and then we took justin and lance to justin's house to halp justin's mom. And jessi, alex, and I went to alex's house so jessi could do halley's hair. It turned out so cute! lol I did alex's hair and burned him with the curling iron lol oops sorry! Then we went cosmic bowling which was coolio, because Riana, nate, Alyssa, julia, and david all showed up! After that Lnace, alex, jessi, halley and I went back to alex's house and watched the simpson's. I tried to keep the guys up but it didn't happen, so jessi and I left around 1 lol. 

Sunday: Jessi and I were super late for Sunday School....what's new? We tried to come up with an amazing story on why we were late but i don't think anyone believed us....lol. Pastor Jon gave an amazing sermon. I was like whoa dang! I got to see Mr. Steve, Debbie, and Robin which rocked! After church Justin and Lance came over to my house for lunch and then we took lance to work. Justin and I went to jessi's house ....lol I fell asleep like usual. Then we had to be back at church at 4:30 so chris, erin and I could practice. Then we had youth and played volley ball and some weird form of dodge ball that my mom came up with lol "if you can dodge traffic you can dodge balls". After church I took Zach home and then I went home to have "Annie time". 

I have had the worst morning but I'll tell y'all about it later....
later gator!

-annie-

After school I went and picked up Alyssa from school and we went toark's house to chillax with him and Alex. hey hey guys!
So life has been good. School starts back up on Tuesday and I am pretty nervous. Oh well I'll get over it.....
Christian Challenge is back up on Tuesday too! I han't been going to it for the longest time , but I'm gonna start going again. I even got ahold of Liz and Sara, so I might start playing in the band again!
I'm trying to keep in touch with all my friends old and new. I don't really know why but I can see evreyone is hurting lately so I figure everyone needs someone to talk to. It's exciting to hear how everyone is doing good and bad....it shows how God is working and how He is going to work. 
I miss Michelle! I called her yesterday, but really didn't get to talk much. Oh well I'll call her soon, and then maybe we can talk.
I miss Christina too! I've tried calling her lately, but she either doesn't return my calls or she calls me back for like 2 sec. Oh well I'll call her and maybe we can get together!
I have to go...Justin and Lance are here and I think they are making a mess of my kitchen lol
     -annie-

I don't know what to do. I've spent hours in prayer for them, but still nothing.I know God will move but my heart is breaking in the mean time. All I can do is pray because I have to be strong. I have to raise them up in prayer and I need the strength. 
       -annie-
"I will perfect everything that concerns you" psalms 138:8

Its my dad's b-day!

The past week has been stressful. I have had a lot of things on my mind.....i hate thinking sometimes lol. So yep yep I was thinking about schoool and seminary and my future and guys and friends and this summer and family and church and ........so as you can see my mind has been full lately lol. And then the minute I was trying to figure all of this out and how I was going to handle it all God spoke to my heart. I remembered that God has it all under control. That is the one thing I always have to remember to come back to. It is so hard for me to give up control, but things seem to all fall in place once I just hand them over to God. 

This week-end was fun. Friday night Justin, Jessi, Lance, and I all hung out at Jessi's. We had a snowball fight at like 11pm!lol
Saturday I went to Christan's baby shower and video tapped. It was such a nice baby shower and it gave everyone the opportunity to see God at work. It's so exciting to see God's blessings!
Sunday was church of course lol. Then Lynsey, Peggy, Lance, Kylee, Kenny, and I went to eat at a buffet (it was bad) and it was fun to just hang out. Then I had to be back at church at 4 and I started girls group back up. It was an amazing time just sit around, read the bible, and pray with my sisters in Christ. I was so excited to hear their hearts for God!After that I went and picked up Alex and Justin for church. Then we went to youth group and pastor Mike gave and awesome sermon! After church I had to take 7 people home in my little 5 seater sudan lol. I don't think I have ever laughed so hard in my life....but looking on the brite side we all bonded lol. 
Well I guess I should go
talk to ya later gator
love always,
    Annie
P.S. Boys are still bad! lol

HEY HEY Y'ALL!
   I'm sorry I havnt updated in a realy long time, so let me inform you on my o' so exciting life.lol

So my christmas break started about two weeks ago. I guess in college its called "winter break", what is that? Without christmas we wouldn't even have a break.....therefore its christmas break.


Saturday:We had the Christmas play at church, and we were all in it. It was alright...really stressful but alright. After Lance, Alex, Halley, Justin, Mark, and I all went over to Jessi's house to watch a movie. 

Sunday: We had the play again. Lance, Justin, and I got taco bell and hung out at Jessi's again.

Monday: Justin, Jessi, and I went over to Alex's house to chillax. We watched Coolrunnings! I GOT TO TALK TO HANNAH ON THE PHONE! Alex and Justin wanted to watch Kung Pow ( a movie I do not like) so i hid it in the kitchen lol. 

Tuesday: same as monday but we watched Napoleon Dynamite!
